The paper deals with linear codes over finite fields, which is a topic in information theory (cs.IT). The paper also involves algebraic geometry, specifically the study of subfield codes and conic codes, which falls under computational geometry (cs.CG) and algebraic geometry (cs.AG). The paper also discusses the weight distribution of the codes, which is a topic in coding theory (cs.IT). Finally, the paper mentions the Sphere Packing bound, which is a topic in discrete mathematics (cs.DM).
